<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12032k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12032k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12032k"> 32(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mang&eacute; pour mang&eacute; / je pr&egrave;f&eacute;re</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le r&eacute;sultat de l&apos;entretien est demeur&eacute; secret mais il semble bien qu&apos;&agrave; partir du 13 f&eacute;vrier 1783, il ne s&apos;&eacute;leva plus d&apos;incident; les juges du bailliage d&apos;Avranches, saisis, comme on l&apos;a vu, par les religieux d&apos;une requ&ecirc;te introductive d&apos;instance, mirent l&apos;affaire en d&eacute;lib&eacute;r&eacute;. Ce d&eacute;lib&eacute;r&eacute; ne fut jamais vid&eacute;, comme on dit au Palais. Le Contr&ocirc;leur des Guerres n&apos;exigea pas l&apos;ex&eacute;cution des ordres prescrivant la mise en route pour le service des Gardes-C&ocirc;tes des habitants des Quatre Paroisses et ceux-ci reprirent, sans murmurer, leur faction aux portes et sur les remparts du Mont. <p><mark>Mang&eacute;s pour mang&eacute;s, ils pr&eacute;f&eacute;raient</mark> l&apos;&ecirc;tre &agrave; la sauce b&eacute;n&eacute;dictine plut&ocirc;t qu&apos;&agrave; la sauce royale: peut-&ecirc;tre n&apos;avaient-ils pas tout &agrave; fait tort? <br><font color="green">[The result of the interview was kept a secret but it seems that from 13 February 1783 no more incidents occurred; the judges of the bailiwick in Avranches, forced, as we have seen, by the religious to hold an introductory request, began to deliberate. This deliberation was never emptied, as they say in the palace. The Comptroller of Wars did not demand the execution of the order for the prescription of the route for the service of the Gardes-C&ocirc;tes of the inhabitants of the Four Parishes and they took up again, without complaint, their work on the walls and the gates of the Mont. <p> Since there was no escaping being eaten, they preferred to be eaten with a Benedictine sauce rather with a royal one; and who will say they were wrong?]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 192</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
